Y \sim EXP(\frac{1}{2})
 Var(Z-Y) = Var(Z)+Var(Y)  
 \begin{align} Var(Z-Y)&= Var(Z) +  Var(Y)\\ &= \dfrac{(3-1)^2}{12} + \frac{1^2}{2^2} \\ &= \frac{4}{12} + \frac{3}{12}  \\ &= \frac{7}{12} \end{align} 
 \dfrac{4}{12}  + \dfrac{48}{12} = \dfrac{52}{12} = \dfrac{13}{3}   
